<DOC><DOCNO> AP880701-0047 </DOCNO><FILEID>AP-NR-07-01-88 0324EDT</FILEID><FIRST>r i PM-Ex-President-Graft     07-01 0197</FIRST><SECOND>PM-Ex-President-Graft,0202</SECOND><HEAD>Judge Orders Arrest Of Ex-president Accused Of Corruption</HEAD><DATELINE>SANTO DOMINGO, Dominican Republic (AP) </DATELINE><TEXT>   A judge ordered thearrest of former President Salvador Jorge Blanco if he does notreturn from the United States within 15 days to face corruptioncharges.   Judge Juan Maria Severino Tejada announced Wednesday that heordered any qualified Dominican authority to try to capture JorgeBlanco if he does not return. The judge's order also stated thatJorge Blanco will be tried in absentia if he does not appear incourt within 15 days.   Dominican authorities allowed the former president, whocomplained of a heart condition, to fly to Atlanta in May 1987 formedical treatment.   Jorge Blanco, who was president from 1982-86, is one of nearly20 former government officials accused of widespread corruptionduring the former president's administration. They are accused ofmisusing government funds to buy military equipment at inflatedprices and embezzling money from a public food program.   The corruption investigation was ordered by President JoaquinBalaguer after he took office. Blanco has called the charges``political persecution.''   It was unknown whether the former president intended to heed thejudicial order or remain in exile.</TEXT></DOC>